gomodel:SYNGO_5143  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 2, 4: cultured hippocampal and cortical neurons were stained for PIAS3, synaptophysin (SYP) and PSD95 (DLG4) and imaged using both confocal and SIM super-resolution microscopy. PIAS3 was mostly localized to the nucleus with some cytoplasmic localization, but also showed partial co-localization with pre- and post-synaptic marker proteins. Detection levels of PIAS3 at the synapse were generally lower than PIAS1.. Experimental description: M&M: \"For the preparation of primary hippocampal and cortical neurons we employed the protocol previously described by Colnaghi et al.26 Dissected hippocampi and cortexes from two-day-old CD1 mice were incubated ...\"\n\nantibody:\nPIAS3 76 μg/mL (D5F9 XP; Cell Signaling)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-25" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5143" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

